-- Ex-Countrywide Chief Mozilo Will Settle SEC Fraud Probe for $67.5 Million
-- B y   E d v a r d   P e t t e r s s o n
-- 2010-10-15T18:09:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-15/former-countrywide-chief-mozilo-agrees-to-settle-sec-s-fraud-allegations.html
Former Countrywide Financial Corp.
Chief Executive Officer Angelo Mozilo, former Chief Financial
Officer Eric Sieracki and former President and Chief Operating
Officer David Sambol agreed to settle U.S. Securities and
Exchange Commission allegations that they misled investors.  To contact the reporter on this story:
